  Location: Section 5, Ground truth validation
  Attack:   Using one of the models under test (Qwen3) as the primary judge for correctness creates a significant, uncontrolled confound. The judge may have systematic biases that favor its own architectural style or penalize others, regardless of the task difference. The human validation on a small subset of 80 items is insufficient to prove the absence of this bias across the thousands of evaluations perfor...
