--- ADV-A-001 (Reviewer A: Methods Skeptic) ---
  Claim:    "We claim the tensor reveals whether the model is operating in grounded mode (retrieving from stable representations) versus fabrication mode (generating without anchoring)."
  Location: Section 4: Epistemic Signals
  Attack:   This claim fatally conflates two different concepts: a model's computational confidence and its epistemic grounding. The proposed signal, entropy, measures how much certainty the model has in its next-token prediction based on patterns in its training data. It cannot distinguish between a confidently retrieved true fact and a confidently retrieved, but consistently represented, false fact. The pap...
  Defense:  The authors must fundamentally reframe their claim. They should explicitly state that the signal measures computational confidence, not correctness or grounding in external truth. The paper must then ...

