--- ADV-C-001 (Reviewer C: The 'So What?' Reviewer) ---
  Claim:    "An impossibility result for text-only verification with finite budget. Epistemic honesty is unverifiable for systems operating under text-only observation with bounded supervision (sec:formal). The impossibility is structural, not a matter of scale....."
  Location: Section 1: Introduction
  Attack:   The core impossibility result appears to be a formalization of a triviality. The proof demonstrates that a policy conditioned only on a query 'q' cannot distinguish between two world states 'w_A' and 'w_B' that require different outputs. This is not a profound discovery about LLMs or systems; it is a basic property of any function. Framing this as a cornerstone contribution significantly oversells...
  Defense:  Reframe the theorem not as a novel discovery, but as a precise formalization of the architectural flaw in current text-only APIs. Its value is in providing a formal language to critique existing inter...

--- ADV-C-002 (Reviewer C: The 'So What?' Reviewer) ---
  Claim:    "We construct an epistemic observability interface that augments text output with epistemic signals (entropy traces, attention summaries) in a composable tensor format, without architectural changes to current transformers (sec:escape)."
  Location: Section 1: Introduction
